This is a Pidgin/libpurple plugin ONLY for Windows that sets the currently
playing song in Spotify as the Pidgin "Now Listening" status message.

Compiling
---------
To compile this plugin under Windows you have to set up the Pidgin build
environment as explained here: http://developer.pidgin.im/wiki/BuildingWinPidgin

Place the the folder with this plugin's source files into the C:\devel directory
mentioned in the above documentation (or alternatively modify PIDGIN_TREE_TOP in
Makefile.mingw to point to the C:\devel\pidgin-VERSION folder) and execute

make -f Makefile.mingw

Installing
----------
Place the spotify.dll in %APPDATA%\.purple\plugins and the plugin should appear
in the available plugins list.
